You PICKED Path B for this and gave the safe design + 5 risks (cost accumulator, KG writes, verdict ordering, pathB capture race, timeout failure mode). This diff implements it. VERIFY the implementation honors your design and find any NEW concurrency/correctness hole.

## What changed (src/polaris_graph/roles/sweep_integration.py, run_four_role_evaluation)
- New `_compute_claim_results`: COMPUTE-only (run_claim_pipeline per claim). Parallel via ThreadPoolExecutor(max_workers=PG_FOUR_ROLE_CLAIM_WORKERS, default 6). Each claim runs in its OWN `contextvars.copy_context()`; inside, `reset_run_cost()` then return `current_run_cost()` as the per-claim cost delta. Collected BY INDEX (as_completed only assigns index, never drives reduction). Worker exception propagates via future.result() (fail closed). Defensive: any None index -> RuntimeError (fail loud).
- Sequential fast path (workers==1 or <=1 claim): direct call, cost_delta=None -> RecordingTransport keeps the LIVE per-call cap on the parent counter; parent does NOT re-account (byte-equivalent to pre-#1042).
- Parent reduction (unchanged logic) in INPUT order via zip(claims, computed): if cost_delta is not None -> `_add_run_cost(delta)` + `check_run_budget(0)` (BudgetExceededError propagates, never caught; finally only closes KG). Then d8_rows/all_records/final_verdicts/role_call_log/coverage-on-VERIFIED/kg_store.write_claim. KG writes PARENT-only. Incremental role_call_log write per claim.

## Specifically scrutinize (your 5 risks)
