2. KG writes parent-only: confirmed not in workers?
3. Determinism: output order == input order regardless of completion order — confirmed (collect by index, reduce via zip)?
4. pathB capture _SINK: the impl leaves it SHARED (copy_context shares the list by ref; list.append GIL-atomic; call_id used only as an error label by pathB_run_gate, NOT a join/order key). Is leaving it shared SAFE, or does any consumer rely on call_id ordering/uniqueness? (The build agent verified call_id is label-only — confirm.)
5. Timeout failure mode: an exception in any worker fails the whole compute closed (seam HELD upstream, never partial release) — confirmed?

